==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Autoplasty
<hw>Au"to*plas`ty</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Auto-</ets> + <ets>-plasty</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Surg.)</fld>
<def>The process of artificially repairing lesions by taking a piece of
healthy tissue, as from a neighboring part, to supply the deficiency
caused by disease or wounds.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Autopneumatic</ent>⟦br⟧
